   <refnamediv>
       <refname>chis_pdf  </refname>
               <refpurpose>chi-squared probability distribution </refpurpose>
   </refnamediv>
 
        <refsynopsisdiv>
               <title>CALLING SEQUENCE</title>
               <synopsis>[f]=chis_pdf(x,a)</synopsis>
        </refsynopsisdiv>
 
        <refsection>
           <title>PARAMETERS</title>
           <variablelist>
           <varlistentry>
 
           <term>Input</term>
 
<listitem><para>*  <term> x </term> =    a (nxm) matrix</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>*  <term> a </term> =    a scalar or a (nxm) matrix</para></listitem>
 
 
 
<listitem><para>&#160;</para></listitem>
 
           </varlistentry>
 
          <varlistentry>
 
          <term>Output</term>
 
<listitem><para>*  <term> f </term> =    a matrix of pdf at each element of x from chisq(a) or chisq(same element of a) distribution</para></listitem>
 
 
          </varlistentry>
          </variablelist>
        </refsection>
 
        <refsection>
               <title>DESCRIPTION</title>
Returns the pdf at x of the chi-squared(n) distribution.  NOTE: chis_pdf(x,n) = gamm_pdf(x/2,n/2)/2
 
        </refsection>
 
        <refsection>
               <title>EXAMPLE</title>
              <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
y=chis_pdf([1:4],2)
// Provides the (1x4) vectors of probabilities that a chi-square is greater than 1, 2, 3 and 4 respectively.
y=chis_pdf([1:4],2*ones(1,4))
// Do exactly the same thing
 
               ]]></programlisting>
        </refsection>
 
        <refsection>
               <title>AUTHOR</title>
Eric Dubois 2002
        </refsection>
</refentry>
